To make your application Tecla Accessible follow this procedure:

1. Include the package ca.idi.tecla.lib in your application.
2. Create an instance of the class InputAccess( say inputAccess) giving the activity whose options menu has to be made accessible as a parameter to the constructor.
3. Override the onPause() and onResume() methods of the activity.
4. Add the line inputAccess.onPause() to the overriden onPause() method and inputAccess.onResume() to the overriden onResume() method in your activity.
5. Add the return statement inputAccess.onPrepareOptionsMenu(menu) to the method public boolean onPrepareOptionsMenu(Menu) defined in your activity. If you dont have any such method defined, define it.

Note:
1. Method InputAccess.onPrepareOptionsMenu() is overloaded

Demo programs:

Inaccessible version:
https://github.com/rishabhjain08/demo-inputaccesslib/tree/master/DemoInaccessibleOptionsMenu

Accessible version:
https://github.com/rishabhjain08/demo-inputaccesslib/tree/master/DemoAccessibleOptionsMenu